<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="129" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="129">A single female in a poor condition has been collected. This species is easily distinguished by the wholly brownish infuscated wing, which tends to be darker at fore border and along veins; also by the abdomen which is narrow parallel sided with contrasting bands of black and white scales.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
